  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TaC6">
<l>ōō, ulakiṉa tiyalvē yīṉṟō ḷirukka</l>
<l>maṇainī rāṭṭi paṭaittiṭan tuṇṭumiḻn</l>
<l>taḷantu tērntula kaḷikkum mutaṟperuṅ</l>
<l>kaṭavu ṇiṟpa puṭaippala tāṉaṟi</l>
<l>teyvam pēṇuta ṟaṉātu</l>
<l>pullaṟi vāṇmai poruntak kāṭṭi</l>
<l>kolvaṉa mutalā vallaṉa muyalu</l>
<l>miṉaiya ceykai yiṉpu tuṉpaḷi</l>
<l>toṉmā māyap piṟaviyu ṇīṅkā</l>
<l>paṉmā māyat taḻuntumā naḷirntē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Ah, the nature of the world! As the great first god stands by,</l>
<l>who takes care of the world – while she who did not give birth sits –</l>
<l>by bathing the earth, creating [it], digging [it] up,</l>
<l>eating, spitting out, measuring [and] understanding [it],</l>
<l>it (the world) suitably shows its ignorance by honouring deities</l>
<l>known to it on many sides,</l>
<l>– such are the actions it makes an effort for, besides</l>
<l>those beginning with killing – without leaving from this birth</l>
<l>of old great illusion that provides pleasure and pain,</l>
<l>it impresses itself into many great illusions, tremblingly.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
